-- Transnet to Spend $1.6 Billion to Boost Coal Export, Times Says
-- B y   A n d r e s   R .   M a r t i n e z
-- 2012-07-15T06:28:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-15/transnet-to-spend-1-6-billion-to-boost-coal-export-times-says.html
Transnet SOC Ltd. plans to spend
13.5 billion rand ($1.6 billion) in the next three years to
boost coal export capacity to 81 million tons, the Sunday Times
reported.  The state-owned company will probably export 75 million
tons in the 12 months through March 2013, up from 68 million
tons in the previous year, the Johannesburg-based newspaper
said, citing Chief Executive Officer Brian Molefe.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Andres R. Martinez in Johannesburg at 
